{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1181380, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "sharkeater", "body": "Inside of razorfen downs.  You'll see his spirit in your path as a friendly, right before getting to Charlga Razorflank. \r\n\r\nFollowing quest is to kill her and bring him her heart.", "date": "2010-11-24T11:54:14-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Correction, both Charlga Razorflank and Spirit of Agamaggan are in Razorfen [b]Kraul[/b] not Downs.", "creationdate": "2010-11-30T12:18:17-06:00", "id": 197281, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1181380, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kilrogrin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 1345029, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vothul", "body": "Agamaggan is one of the Ancients, most of whom have otherwise come back to life in Mt. Hyjal. While the boar demi-god has yet to return to life, his spirit resides in the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=491]Razorfen Kraul[/url] where he tasks adventurers with the death of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=4421]Charlga Razorflank[/url] in order to redeem his children - the quilboar.\n\nHe died 10,000 years ago during the War of the Ancients while fighting the pit lord Mannoroth, sacrificing himself to aid Malfurion and the others to fight Azshara in her palace. He died in the Barrens, his blood creating the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=5075/blood-shard]Blood Shards[/url]. The quilboar greatly revere Agamaggan and await his return.", "date": "2011-02-21T15:59:53-06:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Am I the only one wondering why he wasn't ressurected alongside the other Ancients?", "creationdate": "2011-07-12T15:42:30-05:00", "id": 251955, "rating": 8, "commentid": 1345029, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Warmongering", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Agamaggan was more likely to enter a blind rage than even Goldrinn. Him not being resurrected was, in retrospect, probably a good thing.", "creationdate": "2012-02-23T21:36:15-06:00", "id": 522122, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1345029, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Reignac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-21T16:00:34-06:00", 1, "Vothul"]}
